
[1]church-warden

   CHURCH-WARDEN, n. A keeper or guardian of the church, and a
   representative of the parish. Church-wardens are appointed by the
   minister, or elected by the parishioners, to superintend the church,
   its property and concerns, and the behavior of the parishioners. For
   these and many other purposes, they possess corporate powers.
